            "answer_text": "We have:(a+b+c).(a+b)= (a+b).(a+b+c) (commutativity of `.`)= (a+b).((a+b)+c)= (a+b).(a+b) + (a+b).c (distributivity of `.` over `+`) Beside of that, `(a+b).(a+b) = (a+b)` (Idempotence of `.`), `a + b = (a + b).1` (identity for `.`) so we have = (a+b).(a+b) + (a+b).c= (a+b).1 + (a+b).c= (a+b).(1+c) (distributivity of `.` over `+`)= a + b (because that 1 + c = 1 \u2014 annihilator for `+`) ",
